    "interpretation": "Pairwise-margin SFT fixes teacher-forced chosen-vs-rejected margins but does not yet fix finite-candidate enum top-1 selection. It improves ranking and reduces top-gold margin, especially under the 5-way pair-observed policy, but all held-out cases still select the wrong candidate.",
